# Package Management - Always Use Yarn

This project uses Yarn as its package manager. Never use npm or pnpm commands.

## Installation
- Use `yarn install` to install dependencies
- Use `yarn add <package>` to add a new dependency
- Use `yarn add -D <package>` to add a development dependency
- Use `yarn workspace <workspace-name> add <package>` to add a dependency to a specific workspace

## Scripts
- Use `yarn <script-name>` to run scripts defined in package.json
- Use `yarn workspace <workspace-name> <script-name>` to run a script in a specific workspace

## Monorepo Management
- The project uses NX for monorepo management
- Run NX commands with `yarn nx <command>`

## Examples
- Installing dependencies: `yarn install`
- Adding a dependency: `yarn add lodash`
- Adding a dev dependency: `yarn add -D jest`
- Running a script: `yarn test`
- Adding to workspace: `yarn workspace @spark-stacker/spark-app add axios`
